  "website": "https://www.wens.com.cn",
  "description": "Wens Foodstuff Group Co., Ltd., together with its subsidiaries, engages in the agricultural and animal husbandry businesses in China and internationally. It operates through five segments: Aquaculture Industry; Engineering and Equipment Manufacturing; Meat Processing; Animal Health Industry; and Other Industries. The company breeds, farms, and sells livestock and poultry, including chickens, pigs, ducks, geese, pigeons, waterfowls, laying hens, and other breeds. It also offers room and low temperature dairy products; poultry and livestock products; chicken, pork, fresh eggs and related products, cooked food, and raw milk under the Wens brand name. In addition, the company is involved in livestock and poultry slaughtering and deep processing, as well as dairy processing; farm planning and design, civil engineering, agricultural and livestock equipment manufacturing and procurement, IoT environmental control, environmental protection, and breeding services; financial investment, industrial investment, and merger and acquisition businesses; and veterinary biological products, veterinary drug preparations, and feed additives. It exports its products. The company was formerly known as Guangdong Wens Foodstuff Group Co., Ltd. and changed its name to Wens Foodstuff Group Co., Ltd. in August 2018. Wens Foodstuff Group Co., Ltd. was founded in 1983 and is headquartered in Yunfu, China.",
